There's no existing project in the directory. Here's the implementation pattern you need:

**1. Create `Middleware/ApiExceptionHandler.cs`:**

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

namespace YourApp.Middleware;

internal sealed class ApiExceptionHandler(ILogger<ApiExceptionHandler> logger)
    : IExceptionHandler
{
    public async ValueTask<bool> TryHandleAsync(
        HttpContext httpContext,
        Exception exception,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var (statusCode, title) = exception switch
        {
            KeyNotFoundException => (StatusCodes.Status404NotFound, "Not Found"),
            ArgumentException => (StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest, "Bad Request"),
            InvalidOperationException => (StatusCodes.Status409Conflict, "Conflict"),
            _ => (0, (string?)null)
        };

        if (statusCode == 0)
            return false; // Let the default handler produce a 500

        logger.LogWarning(exception, "Handled API exception: {Title}", title);

        httpContext.Response.StatusCode = statusCode;
        await httpContext.Response.WriteAsJsonAsync(new ProblemDetails
        {
            Status = statusCode,
            Title = title,
            Detail = title, // Never use exception.Message — it may leak internals
            Instance = httpContext.Request.Path
        }, cancellationToken);

        return true;
    }
}
```

**2. Register in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Services
builder.Services.AddExceptionHandler<ApiExceptionHandler>();
builder.Services.AddProblemDetails();

// Middleware (add early in the pipeline, before MapXxx calls)
app.UseExceptionHandler();
app.UseStatusCodePages();
```

**How it works:**

| Exception | HTTP Status | Detail exposed? |
|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| `KeyNotFoundException` | 404 | Safe title only |
| `ArgumentException` | 400 | Safe title only |
| `InvalidOperationException` | 409 | Safe title only |
| Anything else | 500 | Generic Problem Details, no stack trace |

The `AddProblemDetails()` + `UseExceptionHandler()` combo ensures unhandled exceptions (the `return false` path) produce a 500 response in Problem Details format automatically — no sensitive details included.

Your endpoints stay clean:

```csharp
app.MapGet("/api/items/{id}", (int id, IItemService service, CancellationToken ct) =>
{
    // Just throw — the middleware handles the rest
    return service.GetByIdAsync(id, ct);
});
```
